  Forestry and greening efforts made new headway. The total 
newly afforested area of the province in 1993 was 3.45 million 
mu, a net increase of 740,000 mu over the previous year. 
Forests with commercial value increased in proportion, 
afforestation improved in quality, forestry management was 
strengthened, and total greening area expanded further. 
  Output from animal husbandry increased steadily, with 
further 
increases in the proportion of animals raised to be traded. The 
output of major animal products kept rising and 
livestock-in-fold also increased. 


