  Fishery production maintained relatively fast growth 
momentum. The output of the province's aquatic products in 1993 
was 138,000 tonnes, up 19.7 percent from the previous year. 
  Further improvement was made in conditions for agricultural 
production. By the end of 1993, the aggregate power of the 
province's farm machinery reached 26.24 million kilowatts, a 
growth of 8.2 percent over the end of the previous year. There 
were 1.01 million walking and small tractors, up 11.3 percent; 
42,900 farm produce-carrying trucks, down 0.2 percent; 
irrigation and drainage equipment with a total power capacity of 
6.66 million kilowatts, up 1.5 percent; and 71.138 million mu of 
fields under machine farming, up 1.6 percent. The amount of 
chemical fertilizers applied (100 percent pure) was 2.88 million 
tonnes, a 14.8 percent increase. Power consumption in rural 
areas was 6.11 billion kwh, up 2.5 percent. Effective irrigated 
areas of the province reached 58.02 million mu. However, the 
comparable price structure of farm produce remained irrational, 
socialized services in rural areas remained at a low level, and 
inputs and the incentives for agriculture awaited further 
improvement. 
  Township and town enterprises continued their strong growth. 
According to statistics from the province's bureau for township 
and town enterprises, the total output value of the all the 
province's township and town enterprises was 195 billion yuan, 
up 62.5 percent over the previous year. 
<H5>  II. Industry and the Building Industry </H5>
  The development of secondary industry increased rapidly. 
Industrial production maintained rapid growth momentum, and 
production matched better with sales. The growth value of the 
province's industry in 1993 amounted to 67.573 billion yuan, up 
22.1 percent over the previous year. Of this total, state-owned 
industry grew by 7.2 percent, collective enterprises 29.8 
percent, and large and medium-sized enterprises 15 percent. 
  There was adjustment in the industrial structure, with a 
notable market orientation and all-round development in light 
and heavy industry. The annual value of growth of light 
industry was 30.821 billion yuan, up 20.8 percent over the 
previous year, and that of heavy industry was 36.752 billion 
yuan, up 23.3 percent. Increases and decreases in product 
output reflected changes in market demand and supply and the 
effects of state macroregulatory and control policies. The 
output of products welcomed by the market grew faster. 


